  "original_title": "\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9f\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dd0\u0db4\u0dca. 15\u0daf\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0db3\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sep. to the wheat flour issue. Solutions by 15th",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Trade and Food Security Minister Mr. Naleen Fernando said in a press conference in Ja-Ala that by September 15, the wheat flour problem we are facing will be solved and the rising bread prices will disappear.",
        "Mr. Naleen Fernando said here that although the two companies working to import the wheat flour needed by the country faced some problems while importing the wheat due to the dollar problem, the necessary facilities were provided to those institutions under the Indian loan scheme. But the minister pointed out that the country faced a big problem in importing wheat flour due to the fact that the import of wheat became a problem due to the Russian-Ukrainian military conflicts and India stopped exporting their flour. He expressed confidence that the bread flour problem in the country will be resolved by the 15th of the month.",
        "Mr. Naleen Fernando also said that during the discussions held with wheat importing companies, it was revealed that they have enough wheat for about a month. Accordingly, the Minister of Trade and Food Safety disclosed in the press conference that he was instructed to flour the wheat and present it to the market and that the consumer authority has been instructed to check the amount of flour released by the companies to the market once every week.",
        "In the same way, Mr. Naleen Fernando said that in the upcoming discussion with the bakery owners' association, they would request that no decisions be made at this moment regarding the price of bread and that they cannot close their eyes while the people of this country are suffering from high cost of living. Therefore, the Minister of Trade and Food Safety stated that he has instructed the consumer authority to find out whether the prices set for flour by dairy companies are reasonable."
      ],
